   "source": [
    "### Split into train and test data sets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(316813,) (105605,) (316813,) (105605,)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train,X_test, y_train,y_test = train_test_split(news_df['TITLE'],news_df['CATEGORY'], random_state=1 )\n",
    "\n",
    "print(X_train.shape,X_test.shape,y_train.shape,y_test.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Extract features\n",
    "\n",
    "Apply bag of words processing to the datas"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer\n",
    "\n",
    "count = CountVectorizer(stop_words='english')\n",
    "\n",
    "training_data  = count.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "test_data  = count.transform(X_test)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Train Multinomial Naive Bayes classifier"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n",
    "\n",
    "bayes = MultinomialNB()\n",
    "\n",
    "bayes.fit(training_data,y_train)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate predictions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "predictions = bayes.predict(test_data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Evaluate model performance\n",
    "This is a multi-class classification. So, for these evaulation scores, explicitly specify average = weighted"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
